: "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Prayer request.  Our community is grieving a tragic motorcycle accident, at 17, Military Cadat, Montana Masker riding with her brother 19, Cody, still in ICU.  Montana knew and loved God. A verse that she loved and lived by was Philippians 4:13. She knew she could do all things through Christ. \ud83d\ude4f\n\n", "last_comment_created": 1773937384944, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 1, "score_up": 89, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"description": "Montana Elizabeth Masker, 17, of Wilmington, went to be with the Lord on March 8, 2026. Montana brought light and energy to everyone who had the privilege of knowing her.Montana was a student at First State Military Academy where she proudly held the rank of Captain. She was known for her leadership, dedication, and the strong presence she brought to her school community. Montana was lovingly known to her Marine Instructors as \u201cBig Sky.\u201d", "large_image": "Jm6vAfBu5CyZk5wD.png", "title": "Masker, Montana Elizabeth - McCrery & Harra"}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASGJ2OYB5", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 121, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8498807, "raw_content": "", "author": "Tailgunnerjoe", "created": 1773926075361, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "WuFluHoax", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "truthsocial.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASGJ2OYB5.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://truthsocial.com/@JudicialWatch/116256002539221454", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"